flowRoot.flowPara: Openwear is a collaborative platform for fashion creation that wants to promote an alternative approach to fashion through an open source brand and an online community. Open Design, therefore, is not limited to furniture and product design but can also applied successfully to fashion and brand design.

Openwear consists also of an online community where designers can share values, access to knowledge and practice of collaborative and distributed work. It is where makers, fashion producers, small local enterprises, educational institutions can network to participating in the production of a new vision of fashion based on micro-communities and sustainability.

Openwear is an open brand. Openwear is a type of collective trademark that recognizes the productive role of co-production, engages in strategies that aim at redistributing the value thus produced and seeks organizational solutions that give co-producers a say in determining the overall governance of the brand. Openwear tries to institutionalize mechanisms of revenue sharing through which co-creating consumers can benefit from the value that they produce.
